7:
Phew... We can finally relax. With
everything that's happened, it hasn't
been easy.
10:
We can't sit around for too long
though. There's still the matter of
finding a way back to our world.
13:
I hope we can get on that fast,
especially since Romero's gone
missing too.
17:
We should probably expect to stay
in this Saga for the time being.
26:
I found all of our makeup and music
equipment in the labyrinth earlier...
29:
Which means we're going to save
Saga by saving the Sagas of both
Japan and this world! Go,
Franchouchou!
34:
Hold on a second! You mean we're
going to be idols here too?!
40:
You bet! Idols will "live" on in the
Sagas of both worlds!
49:
I was worried about keeping my
singing and dancing skills up, so this
works for me.
57:
Not like we've got anything better to
do right now. Might as well live it up
as idols in the meanwhile!
63:
I've already got idol stuff lined up for
you! No time to slack! Get ready to
get out there and show them what
you're made of!
70:
Wait! How is everyone okay with
this?!
77:
Alk and his friends will be helping us
starting today! Give them a round of
applause!
83:
You're going to treat these grounds
as your lesson studio. Now carry on!
My next order of business awaits!
88:
I sure didn't expect us to be helping
with your idol activities.
91:
I apologize for our producer making
such a sudden request...
95:
Oh, it's fine. We're kind of curious
actually.
100: Yes. The idea of idols intrigues me.
104:
Fascinating. Especially impressive is
how they move their arms and legs
independent of each other while
dancing to the music.
107:
Their timing was a bit off during that
spin though.
118:
Let's start from the top again. Our
movements might have gone
sluggish since we're so used to
being zombies.
123:
Yeah, I suppose there's room for
improvement. But maybe we can
take a little break firs—
129:
All that sound must've drawn the
monsters. Let's go, Nimbus!
147: Sorry about that! Is everyone okay?!
150:
F-fortunately, yes. Big thanks to
Tae-chan too.
154:
Tae is a most proficient biter. Truly
brave.
160:
A proficient biter? I sure hope her
jaw's okay...
166:
Oh, about that! Um, she just has an
incredibly sturdy jaw! Right,
Tae-chan?
171:
We were too naive. If we want to be
idols in this world, we might have to
learn to fight too.
177:
I'd be cool with that! I wouldn't mind
being the best as more than just
idols!
182: In that case, I want to be a mage!
188:
I can't believe this! Aren't you all
taking to life in this world a little TOO
easily?
192:
I am pleased to see such motivation
from everyone.
197:
Oh, I just remembered. You're going
to need some equipment to hold a
concert, aren't you?
201:
Yeah, our producer mentioned we'll
have to look for some.
204:
Okay, leave the equipment to us.
There are things you'd probably
have trouble acquiring on your own
anyway.
207:
Ah! But we wouldn't want to impose
on you...
212:
It is no bother at all. This will give you
more time to focus on practice
sessions.
217:
Yeah, we really want to help. As long
as it's okay with you.
222:
It's more than okay! Seriously, we
can't thank you enough... We'll
double our efforts to put on a great
show!
227:
Sakura-han? What's with the pained
expression?
231:
These people are so nice to us. It
hurts that I can't tell the truth about
ourselves; it's like I'm deceiving
them...
234:
Hm, no way around that, is there.
We're zombies after all.
247:
Wow! You even brought us mics and
in-ear monitors! This is perfect!
250:
For sure... How did you manage to
secure all this equipment?
254: We had to go to many places.
258:
Truth is, we happen to have
connections in the idol business.
262:
With all of this, doing a concert in
this world's not a pipe dream
anymore!
267: I'm glad you like the selection.
271:
Mm-hm! I can already tell the
concert's going to be a success!
